      <h2>Polyvalent Heat Pumps for Commercial Use</h2>
      <p>
        Our polyvalent heat pump technology scales from residential to commercial applications. Unlike conventional heat pumps that produce either heating or cooling, our system produces <strong>both simultaneously</strong> — delivering an effective COP of 7:1.
      </p>
      <p>
        For commercial buildings with concurrent heating and cooling loads (which is most buildings), this means substantially lower energy costs compared to running separate heating and cooling systems.
      </p>

      <h2>Applications</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Commercial hot water</strong> — high-volume domestic hot water for hospitality, healthcare, and aged care</li>
        <li><strong>Space heating and cooling</strong> — via hydronic radiant ceiling panels or other distribution systems</li>
        <li><strong>Process heating</strong> — low-temperature process heat for food, beverage, and manufacturing</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Advantages Over Conventional Systems</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Lower operating costs</strong> — 3–7x more efficient than direct electric heating, and eliminates gas dependency</li>
        <li><strong>No gas required</strong> — fully electric, can be powered entirely by solar</li>
        <li><strong>Simultaneous output</strong> — generates hot and cold water at the same time, capturing energy that conventional systems waste</li>
        <li><strong>Scalable</strong> — multiple units can be configured for larger commercial loads</li>
      </ul>

